Bug Tracker Admin Data Examples
================================

This file explains what kind of information you can enter in each admin module.


Project
-------
Project means the application, website, or system where the bug is found.

Example 1:
Name: Library Management System
Description: Web app for managing books, students, borrowing, and returns.

Example 2:
Name: E-Commerce Website
Description: Online shopping platform with cart, payment, and order tracking.

Example 3:
Name: Student Attendance System
Description: Application for marking attendance and generating attendance reports.


Bug
---
Bug means the actual issue or problem reported in a project.

Example 1:
Title: Login button not working
Description: When the user enters valid username and password, the page refreshes but does not log in.
Project: Library Management System
Status: Open
Priority: High
Assigned to: smith
Reported by: gokula

Example 2:
Title: Payment page shows server error
Description: Checkout fails with a 500 error after selecting UPI payment.
Project: E-Commerce Website
Status: In Progress
Priority: Critical
Assigned to: gokula
Reported by: smith

Example 3:
Title: Attendance report downloads empty file
Description: The generated attendance report file opens, but it has no student records.
Project: Student Attendance System
Status: Open
Priority: Medium
Assigned to: smith
Reported by: gokula


Comment
-------
Comment means a discussion, update, or note added to a bug.

Example 1:
Bug: Login button not working
Author: smith
Content: I checked the browser console. There is a JavaScript error on the login page.

Example 2:
Bug: Payment page shows server error
Author: gokula
Content: Fixed the payment callback URL. Please test the checkout flow again.

Example 3:
Bug: Attendance report downloads empty file
Author: smith
Content: The database query is returning records, so the issue may be in the report generation code.


